name: Income, Inheritance, Registration and Stamp Tax Treaty(1982)
Income, Inheritance, Registration and Stamp Tax Treaty(1970)
Status:
Status: Terminated
Conclusion Date: 27 March 1970/8 June 1970. 
Entry into Force: 23 June 1971 (see NOTE). 
Effective Date: 1 January 1968 (income);23 June 1971 (succession and registration) (see Article 42). 
Termination Date: 1 January 1992.
Note:  This Convention continues to apply to the island of Mayotte. With effect from 2010, Mayotte has become a French overseas department (Département d'Outre Mer, DOM) instead of its former status of French overseas territory (Territoire d'Outre Mer, TOM). According to the French tax authorities, (Guideline 14 B-1-93 of 13 January 1993), this Convention no longer applies to the Federal Islamic Republic of the Comoros since its independence, 3 January 1976. However, France continues to apply its provisions to Comoros-source income attributed, at the latest, to 1991 or to an accounting period closed in 1991. There is no indication as to whether the same applies to French-source income derived by residents of the Comoros. 
NOTE 1:  The treaty article headings reproduced below are unofficial headings prepared by IBFD based on the topic of the treaty articles.

 Effective Date: 1 January 1968 (income); 23 June 1971 (succession and registration) (see Article 42). 
 Termination Date: 1 January 2014.

However, France continues to apply its provisions to Comoros-source income attributed, at the latest, to 1991 or to an accounting period closed in 1991. There is no indication as to whether the same applies to French-source income derived by residents of the Comoros.  This Convention no longer applies to the island of Mayotte, which is a French overseas department (département d'outre-mer, DOM) since 31 March 2011.
